subSubSection.paragraph:
Head.
Brown, with two pairs of tubercles; large occipital tubercles and small sub-occipital tubercles. Maxillae with maxillary canine length greater than relative width (
Fig. 2A
), and with lateral serration (
Fig. 2B
); three-segmented maxillary palp covered with hair-like setae, segment length ratio from base to apex = 3.3:3.4:1 (
Fig. 2C
). Left mandible with three outer incisors and two inner incisors; mandibular incisors not enlarged, densely covered with irregularly ordered hair-like setae on dorsolateral surface (
Fig. 2D
). Right mandible with three outer incisors and two inner incisors, tuft of short setae present in concavity close to molar area, and densely covered with irregularly ordered hair-like setae on dorsolateral surface (
Fig. 2E
). Labium densely covered with hair-like setae; glossae length greater than width; labial palp three-segmented, first and second segments subequal, third segment small (
Fig. 2F
). Labrum densely covered with setae, anterior margin somewhat concave medially (
Fig. 2G
). Hypopharynx: sub-lingua rounded with anterolateral hair-like setae, lingua oval with anterolateral, short setae (
Fig. 2H
).

- a body light brown and a broader shape (
Fig. 1B
);

- abdominal terga having a pair of shorter and smaller tubercles on segments II-IX and the orientation of abdominal tubercles on segment VII–VIII parallel rather than divergent (
Fig. 4F
);
